\n<End City Orphan>Papa's in there...\.\.\. I know it.\.\. I've heard his voice...
There's something under the pedestal...\.\.\. it looks heavy,\. but maybe with enough \i[324] \c[18]Strength\c[0]...
The huge Oxen is in the way...\.\.\. it looks heavy,\. but maybe with enough \i[324] \c[18]Strength\c[0]...
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\.\.\. \BST[1]Oh well,\. it's gone now,\. I'll just tell that counter girl I've dealt with that...\.\.\. "mouse"?
This switch has no lever.\.\. You can't turn it on like this...
To every citizen of our beloved End City.
The Self Defense Committee thanks you for the goods you're willing to part from.\.\. Cash \G will be emitted by this Mana powered Offering Box in exchange for your items.
Thank you for using this Offering Box!
\n<\n[3]>You're here.\.\. Let's get moving,\. my contact is waiting inside the building in front of us.
\n<\n[1]>This alchemy shop?\.\. I doubt anyone's in there...\.\.\. no light or sound comes from inside...
\n<\n[1]>Don't get any ideas,\. witch!\.\. If you've got "friends" of your inside waiting for me,\. I'll make you pay for it.
\n<\n[3]>We're not going to the shop,\. cat.
\n<\n[3]>See?\.\. As easy as squishing Melmos,\. for someone like me~!
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\.\.\. stop gloating and lead the way,\. witch.
\n<\n[1]>"End City",\. huh?\.\. I don't like this place one bit...
\n<\n[1]>But if they came this way,\. I'll find them!\.\. I'm sure of it!
\n<\n[1]>Now,\. let's get with this done with.\.\. And quickly.\.\. I'd rather be in a Cucco's Nest than here...
\n<\n[1]>I can't go knocking doors,\. the trail is still fresh!\.\. I'm sure there's something of his around the City!
\n<\n[1]>You!\.\. Big!\.\. Ugly!\.\. Move from the door!\.\. I have to reach the Hole!!
\n<\n[1]>What's with this guy?\.\. I don't like it one bit...
\n<\n[1]>This \ii[20]!\.\. This is mom's,\. just like my \ia[50]!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>DAMN IT!\.\. DAMN THEM ALL!!\.\. HE'S MIIINE!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>YOU HEAR?!\.\. I'LL FIND YOU,\. BASTARDS!!\.\. NO MATTER HOW DEEP YOU GO!\.\. I'LL GET WHAT'S MINE BACK!!
\n<\n[1]>There's no time to lose.\.\. I have to find a way down...
\n<\n[1]>I'll just have to find the biggest house in End City...\.\.\. \BST[7]the one's running the place will be there.
\n<Bird Lady>CAN'T YE SEE THEY'RE IN LOVE?!\.\. SHOW SOME RESPECT TO TH' BIRDIES!
\n<Bird Lady>See all the precious birdies 'round the city?\.\. You'd better not plan to pounce on those pretties,\. you big cat.
\n<\n[1]>I don't eat raw birds,\. you crone.\.\. Feathers are gross...
\n<Bird Lady>Ya can say that now,\. but I see that shine in yer eyes...\.\.\. ye shouldn't fight against yer nature,\. cat.
\n<Bird Lady>The city's full o' birdies during th' day...\.\.\. listen to this old lady...\.\.\. th' azure birds,\. they're smarter than yer average feathered ones...
\n<Farmhand>Oi!\.\. Fresh crops straight from th' fields!
\n<Farmhand>We're allowed t' peddle the ones we don't send down th' Hole,\. 'ts a good way to make a livin' around here.
\n<\N[1]>Uhm...\.\.\. seen a young brat around?\.\. Probably carried around by a pack of thugs...\.\.\. probably someone big and ugly like you...
\n<Farmhand>Oh!\.\. You've got a foul mouth,\. missus...
\n<Farmhand>But no,\. ain't seen nothin' suspicious,\. furry one.
\n<End City Nun>Our Holy Abode shall rise high over End City!\.\. O!!\.\. For the glory of the Hole,\. we'll guide this age of perdition!!
\^\n<\N[1]>I'm looking for a brat!\.\. My brother!\.\. Have you seen\.\.\.
\n<End City Nun>The curse of the Hole is strong within you.\.\. O,\. Godly Hole,\. watching over us from below,\. grant this cursed one your pity~
\^\n<\N[1]>!!\.\.\. ...\.\.\.\.\. \BST[7]...\.\.\. You're lucky I've got no time on my paws right now.
\n<Blood Maid>My Lady,\. Lady Anzu,\. instructed me to guide any stranger around the city she's supervising.
Guide me to your Lady's place.
Guide me to the Potion Shop.
Guide me to your Lady's place.

\n<Blood Maid>The young Lady lives in the \c[18]Blood Manor\c[0],\. North of here.\.\. She recently fell ill,\. so my companions in there won't allow anyone,\. much less a complete stranger,\. to meet her.\.\.
\n<Blood Maid>Any business you may have with Lady Anzu,\. will have to wait.
\n<Blood Maid>If you need to rest,\. the \c[18]Inn\c[0]'s straight East of here,\. close to the edge of the Abyss.
\n<Blood Maid>Just head to Eastern End City from here,\. you can't go wrong.
\n<Blood Maid>The \c[18]Ursa Scale\c[0] is one of the main armories that used to provide blades and armors back when the Company first started colonizing the Hole.
\n<Blood Maid>I heard it went out of business as a result of Manaworks growing popularity.\.\. I've heard the chief of the furnace has been reported missing a while ago.
Guide me to the Potion Shop.
\n<Blood Maid>\c[18]Anemone's Bloom\c[0] is the place to go if you're looking for potions and other drugs made by refining the little mana that reaches here.
\n<Blood Maid>I've heard the manager is a beauty...\.\.\. but nothing compares to Lady Anzu!
\n<Blood Maid>The citizen of End City founded their own \c[18]Hole S\c[0]elf \c[18]D\c[0]efence \c[18]C\c[0]ommittee to organize themselves against the dangers coming up from the Hole's lower Strata.
\n<Blood Maid>The \c[18]SDC\c[0] building is close by,\. I suggest you pay them a visit if you want to make \G and a name for yourself in here.
Guide me to the Public Baths.
Guide me to the Spring Goddess' Shrine.
Guide me to the Abyss Lift.
Guide me to the Public Baths.
\n<Blood Maid>Working all day in the fields or preparing shipments for the Hole can to be tiring~
\n<Blood Maid>That's why a small part of the pure water that gets sent down,\. to the Company's facilities,\. is used in End City's \c[18]Nekofish Bathouse\c[0]!
\n<Blood Maid>The farm are in the Eastern part of End City,\. you have to take the bridge after the Nekofish Bathouse to head there.

\n<Blood Maid>Fresh,\. tasty crops can't grow in the Hole,\. so the citizen of End City have to grow what's needed to sustain the Divers and the employees of the Company that are currently in the depths of the abyss.
Guide me to the Spring Goddess' Shrine.
\n<Blood Maid>The Shrine's in the Eastern part of End City,\. you have to take the bridge after the Nekofish Bathouse to head there.
\n<Blood Maid>The old lady managing the boat to reach the Shrine asks for a small fee,\. you should bring some change with you~
Guide me to the Abyss Lift.
\n<Blood Maid>The Lift is strictly off limits!\.\. If you're not with End City's guards,\. the Oxen won't allow you inside!
\n<Blood Maid>I won't guide you there,\. kitten,\. you're too green to challenge one of those "monsters".
Neneko enters the bath house to see her friend Shina with her head hanging low.\.\.
She had a bad habit of letting things affect her too much,\. but this was out of character even for her.\.\.
Her head perks up as she hears the voice of her friend calling out to her.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>You look...\.\.\. down.\.\. Was it something you ate?
\n<\n[1]>Well,\. anybody with a pair of functioning eyes can see that's a lie.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>But if you don't wanna talk about it,\. suit yourself.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Yeah...\.\.\. I'd rather not dwell on it too much...\.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>I just...\.\.\. I hurt myself a little bit and I wasn't able to work as quickly as I usually can today.\.\. Manager got annoyed,\. I got scolded.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Well,\. what can I say?\.\. \BST[1]If you were out hunting in the forest like me,\. you wouldn't have to worry about stuff like bosses and getting paid.\.\. Nah.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>You'd just make a sweet life for yourself all on your own.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>I guess so...\.\.\. but I'm also not as tough as you so...\.\.\. I don't think I'd manage to make a proper living for myself that way.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>I think I'd probably starve to death pretty fast if I tried that.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Right.\.\. Well,\. I guess you're not wrong about that.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Let's just not talk about it.\.\. I'm here to relax and take my mind off it.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Suits me.\.\. All this talk about things that suck is making me miserable.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Well,\. actually I have some good things I can talk to you about!\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Despite the little setback today,\. our crops at the farm have been growing exceptionally well these past few days.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>They've been growing faster and the harvests yield more too.\.\. More profit for the farm means more security for all of us workers!\.\.
Neko's indifference leads Shina to try and change the subject,\. hoping to discuss something more pleasant with her friend.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>You know,\. I really wonder what could've brought about this sudden increase.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Out of curiosity,\. I looked into some of the farm's records and we haven't had yields this good in the past thirty years.\.\. \BST[6]That's longer than I've been alive!\.\.
\n<\n[4]>But I digress.\.\. \BST[5]Talking about farming and crops probably isn't all that interesting to a cat.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Anything interesting going on with you lately.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Y-\.You wanna just enjoy the bath then?\.\. Just lay back and let the water wash away all the day's troubles?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>You got that right,\. let's just kick back and enjoy.\.\.
Neko lets out a satisfied purr as she adjusts her position and closes her eyes to better relax herself.\.\.
\n<\n[4]>Warm water's always got it's way of making the weary relax,\. huh?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>What's with you today,\. can't remember the last time I saw ya this hyper.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>I know,\. buuuuuuuut!\.\. I got a nice,\. big ol' tip today at work!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Oh,\. you're just gonna be a big,\. ol' show off today,\. aren't you?\.\. Managed to get lucky and get a tip?\.\.
\n<\n[5]>No,\. I don't think it was luck!\.\.\.\.\BST[5] The manager said that I was working r-\.really hard these past few days!\.\.
On one hand,\. what she's saying could possibly be true.\.\. On the other hand,\. Neneko suspects it has a lot less to do with her hard work and more to do with her tits.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>You sure about that?\.\. You sure you didn't try to show any of your 'goods' to get on the manager's good side?\.\.
Neko eyes her friend's chest while making no effort to hide it.
\n<\n[1]>You know,\. those two bountiful harvests right there.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Neko!\.\. H-\.Heavens,\. no!\.\. I would never do something like that!\.\. I-\.I'd be t-\.too embarrassed to show off my...\.\.\.my b-\.breasts to the manager!\.\.
Shina's eyes dart around as she struggles to find a way to change the subject.
\n<\n[5]>So,\. uhhh,\. anyway!\.\. I worked really hard and ended up getting the tip!\.\. I was thinking I would share some of it with you!\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Since I don't really need all of the money from the tip,\. I was thinking maybe you could use some of it too!\.\.
\n<\n[5]>No problem!\.\. That's what friends are for,\. right?\.\.
Neko sits in the bath,\. contemplating what she could do with the extra money she had just stumbled into out of nowhere.
For now she was just thinking of all the different kinds of fish meals she could buy.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>You look a little troubled,\. Neko.\.\. Is everything okay?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I just wasn't expecting to get money out of nowhere like this,\. ya know?\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Awww,\. Neko.\.\. You can spend it on anything you like!\.\. I kept plenty for myself too!\.\.
\n<\n[5]>But if you want any ideas,\. I'm more than happy to help.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>You know,\. whenever I've got some spare money lying around,\. what I end up doing is buying this really tasty salad they have at the bar across here!\.\.
\n<\n[5]>It's a little bit on the expensive end,\. so I don't usually indulge myself,\. but when I do!\.\. \BST[4]Hoooooo boy!\.\. I'm on cloud nine for the rest of the day!\.\.
\n<\n[5]>They really put the finest veggies in that thing,\. and it's really good for your health too!\.\. We could go get two salads together and eat while we hang out!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Well,\. I'm a cat,\. duh.\.\. I can't eat vegetables,\. they make me sick.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Oh,\. right.\.\. I totally forgot about that...\.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Though you could still come hand out at the bar and just eat something else.\.\. I'm sure they've got plenty of tasty meat dishes there too!\.\.
Neko's ears perked up at the thought of that.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Yeah,\. they probably do.\.\. I'll think about it and we can maybe arrange something.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Alright!\.\. I'll be looking forward to it!\.\.
Neneko spots Shina in the bath,\. though something seems a little bit off about her.\.\.
The cat's stepping in the pool,\. next to her,\. but her friend remains silent.\.\.
Approaching a tiny bit closer,\. she confirms that is indeed the case.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Tch,\. and here I was thinking I'd get some company to chill with during my bath.\.\.
It only takes a few moments however,\. until she gets all too bored and alone with the silence.\.\.
Why'd you have to sleep on me now?\.\. Of all the damn times!\.\.
As Neko approaches her friend however,\. she soon comes face to face with her friend's 'superior' figure.\.\.
Though she tries to get the thoughts out of her head,\. Neneko can't look away for long.\.\.
Eyes green with envy,\. she remains fixated on her friend's body as she analyzes her figure.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Why the hell are yours so big anyway?\.\. Stupid cow juggers.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Bet you fell asleep like this to show off,\. didn't you?\.\.
Neko steps out of the bath,\. and when she returns,\. she's brought back a bucket with her to carry out a devious little plan.\.\.
A wicked smile creeps onto the cat's face as she fills up the bucket with water and lifts it up high over Shina's head.\.\.
She brings down the bucket,\. splashing a wave of water over her friend's head.\.\.
Shina wakes up suddenly,\. panicked and in total disarray.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Ahhhhhhhhhh!\.\. What's happening!\.\.?\.\. Who's there?\.\.!\.\. Is my time over?\.\.!\.\. I'm sorry!\.\. I'm sooooooooorryyyyyyyyyyyy!\.\.
She manages to calm down a little bit when she sees her friend standing over her with an empty bucket in her hands,\. clearly betraying the culprit behind her rude awakening.\.\
Shina looks up at her friend with a pouty face.
\n<\n[1]>Well,\. you were asleep,\. and I tried to wake you up,\. but you weren't waking up.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Really?\.\. Usually if you poke at me a bit I wake up...\.\.\. I wasn't even sleeping that deeply...\.\.\.
Neko briefly wonders if she's gonna back down or double up on her lie.\.\. She soon makes her choice.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Yes,\. really.\.\. I was practically screaming in your ear,\. I was shaking you,\. you weren't waking up at all.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Oh...\.\.\. then I guess you had no choice then.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>I-\.It's okay...\.\.\. I'm sorry I yelled at you.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Eh,\. don't worry about it too much...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>And you know,\. you gotta stop being such a pushover all the time.\.\. Stand up for yourself a bit!\.\.
\n<\n[5]>H-\.Huh?\.\. But I thought you were just trying to wake me up?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Tch,\. I'm talking in general,\. not about now!\.\. You know what,\. just forget it.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Let's just kick back and chill.\.\. It was a long day...
\n<\n[5]>Oh,\. yeah!\.\. That would be cool!\.\. Let's do that!\.\.

The two girls sit around and enjoy the hot springs for a while.\.\. Feeling like she could finally relax with Shina up and around,\. Neko stretches out and listens to her friend go on about her day.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Warm water's always got it's way of making the weary relax,\. huh?\.\.
\n<???>THIS IS UNACCEPTABLE!!\.\. ONE OF MY MEN WAS LAST SEEN CLOSE TO THIS DREADFUL PLACE!!\.\. DON'T PLAY COY,\. YOU MAID!
\n<Captain Aaron>DON'T THINK THIS IS THE END O' IT!\.\. I KNOW YOU'RE HIDING SOMETHING FROM END CITY'S PEOPLE IN THE'E!!
\n<Captain Aaron>AS THE CAPTAIN OF THE SELF DEFENCE COMMITTEE I'LL GET TO TH' BOTTOM OF IT!!
\n<Captain Aaron>I WON'T LET THA' "COMPANY" OF YOURS RUNNING HER BUSINESS AT TH' EXPENSE O' THE SURFACE PEOPLE!
\n<Baker>...\.\.\. there's a counter for a reason,\. cat.
\n<Baker>I can go back making bread now!\.\. My bakery's saved!\.\. Hole be blessed!!
\n<\n[1]>"Hole"?!\.\. Well,\. you're welcome!\.\. Let's see if that Hole of yours saves your shop next time.
\n<Baker>My deepest apologies,\. lady cat.\.\. You've saved my life,\. I will forever be thankful!
\n<Baker>Take this \ii[40],\. for now,\. but stop again whenever you're around!\.\.
\n<Baker>Now that production's resumed,\. I will always have a bit of bread for my saviour!
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\. I...\.\.\. will stop by,\. then.\.\. Free of charge,\. right?
\n<Baker>A free loaf every day for the brave kitten!
\n<Baker>Fresh bread!\.\. Filling divers backpacks since the First Dive!
\n<Baker>I've been an idiot,\. and now I've got no bread to sell...
\n<Baker>Can't even reach the Mana Stoves,\. pa would be ashamed of me...
